cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on color texture analysis using a novel approach of modeling color images as directed complex networks. This approach involves multiscale analysis and topological characterization of the modeled network. Given that the paper deals with image analysis, computer vision (cs.CV) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes sub-categories such as cs.MM (machine learning), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) likely. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques, which makes this sub-category a possibility as well.
